description: Use patch bumps for routine releases
alwaysApply: true
---

# Release Versioning Policy

- For bug fixes, test-only changes, docs updates, CI/workflow tweaks, and non-breaking refactors, bump PATCH only (for example `0.2.2` -> `0.2.3`).
- Do not bump MINOR unless the user explicitly asks for a minor release.
- When bumping version, update both version sources: `pyproject.toml` (`project.version`) and `baar/__init__.py` (`__version__`).
- Do not pre-create release tags manually for version automation; let `.github/workflows/release.yml` create tag/release from `main` after merge.
